<TITLE> Abdul Karim appointed principal secy to PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 24 (bdnews24.com)Md Abdul Karim, bridges division secretary, has been appointed principal secretary to the prime minister. The appointment was made Wednesday afternoon, a senior establishment ministry official told bdnews24.com. The official refused to be named. Abdul Karim was home secretary during the two-year caretaker government. He has also served as secretary for fisheries, commerce and NBR chairman.
